<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening (bars 1-5): G key, alternating I/ii/iii/IV/V chords. LH open voicing root-5th-8ve-3rd. RH light thirds.
- Bars 6-10: Repeat section - same chord progression, varied RH figuration with contrary motion.
- Bar 11: Open texture with rest, ascending inner line in RH over C-Em-D bass.
- Bar 12: Am/D passing chords; chromatic C# in melody acknowledged in RH.
- Bars 13-15: Final climax build - full 4-voice LH, stepwise RH ascent matching melody.
- Bar 16: Passing A major chord (secondary dominant) with full 4-voice LH.
- Bar 17: D-G-Am-D sequence, contrary motion between melody descent and LH rise.
- Bar 18: Full G tonic close.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH ascending line bars 4,9,14 mirrors melody stepwise motion above
- LH maintains smooth voice leading: common tones held between adjacent chords
- Contrary motion bar 17: melody descends D5-B4-A4-G4-A4, LH bass D2→G2

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-5: Moderate density, establishing key
- Bars 6-10: Same material, slight rhythmic elaboration in RH
- Bars 11-13: Brief opening/breath with rests
- Bars 14-17: Fuller texture, climactic motion
- Bar 18: Convergent final tonic
-->
